URL = http://crackedlabs.org/en/


=Description=

"Cracked Labs is a non-profit organization. It was established in 2012 to strengthen a participatory and self-determined use of information and communication technology as well as the free access to knowledge and information – independently from commercial or governmental interests.

Cracked Labs consists of an interdisciplinary and international network of experts in the fields of science, theory, activism, technology, art, design and education and cooperates with public and private parties.

Fields of work / keywords: Surveillance, online tracking, big data, privacy, open source, open knowledge, copyright, ICT policy, serious games, technology-enhanced learning, gamification, social media."


